children.text: The wall insulation has not been installed in under the bath, which will be reducing the effectiveness of the thermal performance.
The relevant Australian Standard AS 3999 Thermal Insulation of Dwellings - Bulk Insulation - Installation Requirements, states in section 5.4.3.1 that
‘Bulk insulation when installed between wall studs shall be in contact with and fit tightly between studs, top and bottom plates and noggings. See Figure 5.4.3.1.1’ .
The missing batts must be fully installed and properly restrained into position prior to plaster installation.
